		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also I don't know it it's needed to initialize the CPU ram between the two VBlank waits.</div><br />It's not. A lot of official games do the vblank waits one after another. It's just that the time between the vblanks is just a very convenient time to clear CPU RAM, as what else do you have to do during nearly 30,000 CPU cycles between vblank #1 and vblank #2?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">About the $700-$702 stuff, I think he's just checking for particular value in theese 3 bytes, to check if it's the first boot or not. So, he doesn't clear $700-$7ff if it isn't the first boot.</div>
<br />Correct.

		

